node.text:
I am thrilled to introduce the first class of Sparkle On Scholars! ✨ With almost 150 applications from exceptional @nationalmtb student athletes across the country, this selection process was challenging to say the least. But these four student athletes really shined. They are joyful and hardworking in their pursuit of their personal goals on and off the bike, but show an equally powerful commitment to becoming advocates and leaders in the cycling community. I can’t wait to work with them and help support their efforts as  they transition to becoming collegiate student athletes! 

Meet the scholars: @darciebushee @toby_hassett @justinpeck03 @gwen_sepp

Thank you so much to my sponsors, NICA and the many hands and hearts that went into making this opportunity possible. A special shout out to Casey at NICA, my super star mom and co-chair Maggie and the entire selection committee for the countless hours you dedicated to this project. Bikes can open a lot of doors. This is just the beginning! #sparkleon #nationalmtb #morekidsonbikes 

@bikeonscott @srammtb @rockshox @syncrosbike

node.text: Ask and you shall receive 😜 Finally giving you an inside look at the fully built out @scottmtbracing sprinter. This vehicle was designed by @frischi_nextlevel to be my race day set up — but has also enabled a lot of weekend adventures and even this emergency clean air training camp. Grateful to have such a fun adventure mobile and can’t wait to take it back to the races next season! 💃🏻✨ #vanlife #sparklewatts #sendtobend  A huge thank you to @eric_lagerstrom for putting this video together!

node.text: I could not be more excited to announce the release of the @teachaids Crash Course Brain Fly-Through. As an athlete, I have suffered multiple concussions and know how scary, confusing and frustrating they can be. I have also seen how reporting your injury, getting accurate information, and taking recovery seriously can make all the difference. I first got involved in this project as an undergrad at Stanford when I had Piya Sorcar as a professor and it is so meaningful to be able to continue my involvement as an athlete. Please watch this video and share it with your kids - research and education are the most important tools we have to understand and combat the long lasting impacts of head injuries ❤️ #protectyourbrain #crashcourse #science 🤓

node.text: To do things you have never done, you must go beyond supposed limits you have never challenged. Earlier this year, the Kate Epic with @katiehall47 pushed those limits. This week, I am attempting to redefine them again. 3 more days of #climbforcovidrelief! Let’s make them count. 👊🏽❤️✨ #keepcalm #climbon #sparklewatts #dreamteam | video @susietheis

node.text: Train hard, recover harder 👊🏽🔥 Using @whoop to track my recovery and sleep has given me real data to understand the role of rest in achieving my best performances. It sounds simple but it’s sometimes the hardest thing! This year my #RESTolution is to become even more of a nap queen and prioritize my mental and physical recovery between big blocks 😴🧘🏻‍♀️ What’s yours? #napqueen #restolution #inthegreen

node.text: “To deny the struggle is to deny the very thing that allows us to triumph in the end.” - Had a chance to reflect on my Olympic experience in an article for the @washingtonpost (link in bio). It wasn’t the story I hoped to write about Tokyo, but it is an honest one that gives a glimpse into what it feels like to try and fail in the pursuit of big goals. Grateful for all of the people in my corner who have helped me turn this experience into fuel for the fire 🔥⚒ pc @gettyimages

node.text: High highs and low lows. I had a tough and disappointing ride yesterday in my first Olympic Games. It wasn’t the performance I had hoped or worked so hard for and, while I know my support team is disappointed alongside me and not in me, I can’t help but feel the weight of my own disappointment in not being able to put together a race worthy of their efforts. No matter the result, I am proud to have represented my country and crossed the finish line as an Olympian. I am so grateful for all of the friends and family that have supported me on this journey and made it an unforgettable experience. Time to reset, refocus and try again❤️ pc @gettyimages

node.text: Tomorrow is race day! I have waited and worked for a long time to be here and I am so grateful to be lining up healthy, strong and ready to give absolutely everything I’ve got. Thank you to all of the people that have supported me through the highs and lows of this journey - but especially to these three who have believed from the beginning that I would some day stand on an Olympic start line. It is belief that gives us the courage to try. LFG 👊🏽🇺🇸✨ #dreamteam #raceready #berelentless #sparkleon

node.text: I’ll have what they’re having… fun 💃🏻✨🕺🏻 As intense as it is preparing for such a big event, I’m reminded every time I get on my bike that it wasn’t just the hard work and focus that got me here - it was also the joy, teamwork and a mad love for this sport. Thanks @bbcopeland for being my rock (and sometimes sitting under it) this week on track 👨🏻‍🔧 #trainhard #dreambig #hopyourhomie #keepitfun #sparkleon
